    "recap_headline": "University of North Florida",
    "recap_text": "DELAND, Fla. -\nNorth Florida Baseball fell in Game 1 of its weekend series at\u00a0Stetson, 7-2, to open Atlantic Sun Conference play at Conrad Park on Friday.\nSophomore utility player\nSeth Alford\nbelted his third home run of the season in the top of the eighth inning. Alford's two-run homer cut North Florida's deficit to 6-2. He finished 1-3 with two RBI, one home run and one run.\nRedshirt junior utility player\nBoone Hosey\nand junior infielder\nMitchell Collins\nadded one single each on the night, respectively. Hosey improved his on-base streak to 10 games and has now tallied a hit in four straight games.\nFreshman right-handed pitcher\nJeremiah Stewart\ndealt 3.0 innings out of the bullpen and allowed just one run on four hits with three strikeouts.\nStetson scored one run in the first inning, five in the third and one in the eighth to bring the score to its eventual final margin.\nNORTH FLORIDA 2, STETSON 7\nPitchers of Record\nWin:\nJames Hays (2-0)\nLoss:\nDakota Stone\n(3-2)\nLine Scores\nSTETSON\n| 7 R, 13 H, 0 E\nNORTH FLORIDA\n| 2 R, 3 H, 1 E\nStatistical Leaders\nNORTH FLORIDA\nSeth Alford\n| 1-3, 1 HR, 2 RBI, 1 R\nJeremiah Stewart\n| 3.0 IP, 4 H, 1 R, 1 ER, 3 K, 1 BB\nSTETSON\nRenzo Gonzalez | 3-4, 2 RBI, 1 R\nUP NEXT\nNorth Florida remains at Conrad Park for Game 2 of its series at Stetson on Saturday, March 14 at 6:30 p.m. ET."
